Docs.summary: Returns the name this points at, or if it does not point at a name. A normal using X.Y.Z; or using static X.Y.Z; will always point at a name and will always return a value for this. However, a using-alias (e.g. using x = ...;) may or may not point at a name and may return here. An example of when that may happen is the type on the right side of the = is not a name. For example using x = (X.Y.Z, A.B.C);. Here, as the type is a tuple-type there is no name to return.
